          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "Euthantos Embracee, you have tried to connect with the tremere highericy but can't your self destructive nature has had you move to the war front. Maybe you will find a sense of conection in the war. (Source: Mage)",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "POS/RJ"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up on the frontier, the child of an undertaker and a midwife. When death came to your tiny town, you would help your father embalm and dress the dead. And when life came, you would take your mother to the homes of birthing women. And though you were never allowed in the room itself, you learned how to be helpful in other ways, and always enjoyed hearing a baby cry out its first breath. The juxtaposition left an impression on your young mind. New babies and old men had the same squished, wrinkly faces. People cried at birth, and at death. As for you, you went into the seminary as a young boy, your mind fixed on these topics. But it wasn't until you were thrown from a train that you really felt death, and in that moment, you Awakened. The Euthanatos were a natural fit for someone with your inclinations, and you happily joined them, taking to their philosophy like a fish to water. But then the unthinkable happened. Some Tremere asshole thought you'd be perfect for the War Effort, and brought you over into the clan. You raged for several years, your superiors content to let you have your tantrum as long as they were allowed to study your mage blood. However, with your Avatar replaced by a Beast, you lost the tranquil peace you had found as a Euthanatos. Your resolve and fatalism became a love of chaos and destruction. You still try to hold to the ethics of your former order, though you often find this pushes you more into the 'death' sphere than the 'life' or 'rebirth' ones. As a result, your superiors aren't sure what to do with your destructive tendencies. Unwilling (yet) to end a valuable asset, they're sending you to LA where they hope you can be of use to the war effort."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Geraldine",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Tremere - Easily Bound"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1914.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "London",
          "",
          "Generation",
          "Ancilla 9"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "Cody West (Assamite)",
          "You were always interested in the Assamites, the clan of Assassins, but could never get close to them until recently. Now that they're in the Camarilla, you're interested in talking to them about death and undeath. Cody is the name you keep hearing."
        ],
        [
          "Susan Grimm (Brujah)",
          "A Brujah chemist with her own chemistry lab? What's not to like?"
        ],
        [
          "Alistair Ross (Toreador)",
          "You've heard rumors that he's been involved in explosions and he might be useful as an ally."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "You know that you are running out the patience of your superiors. You try, but you just can't make it work with the hierarchy. Do what you can to make Los Angeles work for you (you've heard they're lax with rules)"
        ],
